    "id": "script_commander_cc30",
    "name": "Commander dies \u2014 player chooses to return to command zone",
    "description": "p1's commander Llanowar Elves is on the battlefield. p2 casts Doom Blade targeting it. Llanowar Elves would go to the graveyard; p1 chooses to redirect it to the command zone instead (CR 903.9b). Tests the SBA + replacement effect for commander zone return.",
    "cr_sections_tested": [
      "903.9b",
      "704.6",
      "601.2",
      "608.2"
    ],
    "corner_case_ref": 19,
    "tags": [
      "commander",
      "commander-death",
      "command-zone-return",
      "zone-replacement"
    ],
    "confidence": "high",
    "review_status": "pending_review",
    "reviewed_by": null,
    "review_date": null,
    "generation_notes": "CR 903.9b: if a commander would go to a graveyard or exile, its owner may choose to move it to the command zone instead. The engine implements this as a replacement effect registered at game start. When Doom Blade resolves, Llanowar Elves is destroyed; the replacement effect intercepts the zone change and the engine emits CommanderZoneReturnChoiceRequired. p1 chooses to send it to command zone. The pending_commander_zone_choices mechanism handles this. Initial: p1's Llanowar Elves is on battlefield as commander; p2 has Doom Blade with {1}{B}.",
    "disputes": []
  },
